## Writing Page Objects

All Page Objects extend `BasePage`. The base class provides:

- **Navigation** — `navigateTo()`, `waitForPageLoad()`, `waitForNetworkIdle()`
- **Waits** — `waitForElement()`, `waitForLoadingIndicator()`
- **Assertions** — `expectTitle()`, `expectURL()`, `expectVisible()`, `expectHidden()`, `expectText()`, `expectToast()`
- **Interactions** — `click()`, `fill()`, `selectOption()`, `scrollIntoView()`
- **Attachments** — `takeScreenshot()`
- **Checks** — `isVisible()` (returns boolean, does not throw)

### Example

```typescript
import { Locator, Page, TestInfo } from "@playwright/test";
import { BasePage } from "./BasePage";

export class DashboardPage extends BasePage {
    // Declare all locators as private readonly
    private readonly welcomeHeading: Locator;
    private readonly newInvoiceButton: Locator;

    constructor(page: Page, testInfo: TestInfo) {
        super(page, testInfo);
        this.welcomeHeading    = page.getByRole("heading", { name: /welcome/i });
        this.newInvoiceButton  = page.getByRole("button", { name: "New Invoice" });
    }

    // Expose business-oriented methods — not implementation details
    async expectDashboardLoaded(): Promise<void> {
        await this.expectVisible(this.welcomeHeading, "Welcome heading");
    }

    async openNewInvoice(): Promise<void> {
        await this.click(this.newInvoiceButton, "New Invoice button");
        await this.waitForPageLoad();
    }
}
```

### Conventions

| Rule | Example |
|---|---|
| Extend `BasePage` | `class DashboardPage extends BasePage` |
| Locators: `private readonly` | `private readonly submitBtn: Locator` |
| Business-oriented methods | `submitInvoice()` not `clickButton3()` |
| Use `test.step()` in tests | Not inside Page Object methods |
| One class per file | `DashboardPage.ts` in `src/pages/` |

