## Writing Tests

Always import `test` and `expect` from `../../fixtures/test`, **never** directly from
`@playwright/test`. This gives all tests access to application fixtures and lifecycle
logging automatically.

```typescript
import { test, expect } from "../../fixtures/test";
import { DashboardPage } from "../../pages/DashboardPage";
import ENV from "../../config/env";
import logger from "../../logging/logger";

test.describe("Dashboard", () => {
    test("Dashboard loads after login @smoke", async ({ page, loginPage }, testInfo) => {

        test.info().annotations.push(
            { type: "Suite",       description: "Dashboard"    },
            { type: "Environment", description: ENV.TEST_ENV   },
        );

        await test.step("Log in", async () => {
            await loginPage.open();
            await loginPage.loginWithEnvCredentials();
            logger.info("Authenticated");
        });

        await test.step("Verify dashboard", async () => {
            const dashboard = new DashboardPage(page, testInfo);
            await dashboard.expectDashboardLoaded();
            await dashboard.takeScreenshot("dashboard");
            logger.info("Dashboard verified");
        });
    });
});
```

### Test conventions

| Convention | Detail |
|---|---|
| Import `test` from fixtures | `import { test } from "../../fixtures/test"` |
| Tag smoke tests | Add `@smoke` to the test name string |
| Wrap steps in `test.step()` | Produces readable HTML report output |
| Add annotations | `test.info().annotations.push(...)` |
| Screenshots on key steps | `await page.takeScreenshot("step-name")` |

