## Fixtures

`src/fixtures/test.ts` extends the Playwright `test` object with:

| Fixture | Type | Description |
|---|---|---|
| `loginPage` | `LoginPage` | Pre-instantiated LoginPage for use in any test |
| `_testLifecycle` | `void` (auto) | Logs test start, pass, and failure automatically |

The `_testLifecycle` fixture is applied to **every test automatically** — you do not
need to include it in the test's destructured parameters.

To add application fixtures for future screens, extend `test` in this file:

```typescript
// src/fixtures/test.ts
dashboardPage: async ({ page }, use, testInfo) => {
    await use(new DashboardPage(page, testInfo));
},
```

