## Logging

Use the singleton logger in Page Objects and test files:

```typescript
import logger from "../logging/logger";

logger.info("Navigated to dashboard");
logger.warn("Retry attempt 1 of 3");
logger.error("Login failed — check USERID/PASSWORD in .env");
logger.debug("Response body", { status: 200, body: responseJson });
```

Output format:

```
[2025-06-15 09:23:41] INFO  Navigated to dashboard
[2025-06-15 09:23:42] ERROR Login failed — check USERID/PASSWORD in .env
```

Control verbosity via `LOG_LEVEL` in `src/config/.env`:

| Level | When to use |
|---|---|
| `error` | Failures and unexpected states only |
| `warn` | Recoverable issues |
| `info` | Normal test flow (default) |
| `debug` | Verbose output for local debugging |

