## Environments

Environment-specific values live in separate `.env` files:

```
src/config/
├── .env                     Shared defaults (loaded first)
<%- environments.names.map(env => `├── .env.${env.padEnd(22)} ${env}-specific overrides`).join('\n') %>
```

All files are gitignored. Run against a specific environment:

```bash
<%- environments.names.map(env => `npm run test:${env}      # TEST_ENV=${env}`).join('\n') %>
```

Access environment values in code via the typed `ENV` wrapper:

```typescript
import ENV from "../config/env";

const url   = ENV.URL;       // base URL of the application
const env   = ENV.TEST_ENV;  // active environment name
const user  = ENV.USERID;    // test user identifier (may be undefined)
```

