## CI Integration

Set the following secrets/variables in your CI pipeline:

```yaml
# GitHub Actions example
env:
  CI: "true"
  URL: ${{ secrets.APP_URL }}
  USERID: ${{ secrets.TEST_USERID }}
  PASSWORD: ${{ secrets.TEST_PASSWORD }}
  TEST_ENV: <%- environments.default %>
```

The framework behaves differently in CI automatically:

| Behaviour | Local | CI |
|---|---|---|
| Retries | 0 | 1 |
| Workers | CPU auto-detect | 1 (avoids session conflicts) |
| Max failures | unlimited | 3 (preserves CI minutes) |
| Console logs | enabled | suppressed (set `LOG_LEVEL=debug` to override) |
| `forbidOnly` | off | on (prevents accidental `.only` in PRs) |

